Title: The spatial structure of screening propagators in hot QCD  
Author: Claude Bernard, Michael C. Ogilvie Thomas A. DeGrand Carleton DeTar Steven Gottlieb, A. Krasnitz R. L. Sugar D. Toussaint 
Address: St. Louis, MO 63130, USA  Boulder, CO 80309, USA  Salt Lake City, UT 84112, USA  Bloomington, IN 47405, USA  Santa Barbara, CA 93106, USA  Tucson, AZ 85721, USA  
Affiliation: Department of Physics, Washington University,  Physics Department, University of Colorado,  Physics Department, University of Utah,  Department of Physics, Indiana University,  Department of Physics, University of California,  Department of Physics, University of Arizona,  
Abstract: We use numerical simulations to study the spatial structure of a quark and an antiquark in the imaginary time excitations which mediate the Debye screening of color singlet sources in the high temperature phase of QCD. We find that these correlation functions are very similar to the zero temperature wave functions of the corresponding particles. This result is in conflict with a model of the plasma as a gas of free quarks, in which the static correlation function between a quark and an antiquark would extend over the entire lattice. 
